{"title_page": "2019\u201320 Lehigh Mountain Hawks men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n|mode=Basketball\n|year=2019\u201320\n|prev_year=2018\u201319\n|next_year=20\u201321\n|team=Lehigh Mountain Hawks\n|image=Lehigh Athletics wordmark.png\n|image_size=250\n|conference=Patriot League\n|short_conf=Patriot\n|record=11\u201321\n|conf_record=7\u201311\n|head_coach=[[Brett Reed (basketball)|Brett Reed]]\n|hc_year = 13th\n|asst_coach1=[[Quinn McDowell]]\n|asst_coach2=Harry Morra\n|asst_coach3=Noel Hightower\n|stadium=[[Stabler Arena]]\n|champion= \n|bowl=\n|bowl_result=\n}}\n{{2019\u201320 Patriot League men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2019\u201320 Lehigh Mountain Hawks men's basketball team''' represented [[Lehigh University]] during the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The Mountain Hawks, led by 13th-year head coach [[Brett Reed (basketball)|Brett Reed]], played their home games at [[Stabler Arena]] in [[Bethlehem, Pennsylvania]] as members of the [[Patriot League]]. They finished the season 11\u201321, 7\u201311 in Patriot League play to finish in a tie for eighth place. They defeated [[2019\u201320 Loyola Greyhounds men's basketball team|Loyola (MD)]] in the first round of the [[2020 Patriot League Men's Basketball Tournament|Patriot League Tournament]] before losing in the quarterfinals to [[2019\u201320 Colgate Raiders men's basketball team|Colgate]].\n\n==Roster==\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=2019|team=Lehigh Mountain Hawks|teamcolors=y|high_school=yes}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Jakob|last=Alamudun|num=0|pos=F|ft=6|in=6|lbs=225|class=fr|rs=|home=[[Huntington Beach, California]]|high_school=[[Marina High School (Huntington Beach, California)|Marina High School]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Jeameril|last=Wilson|num=1|pos=F|ft=6|in=7|lbs=200|class=so|rs=|home=[[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]]|high_school=[[Notre Dame College Prep]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|fir